  pm-cfed,related,"2026-07-10T10:48:01.400Z",null,null
body: "Observed live 2026-07-10: `pm activity --from <ts> --compact --json` returns an envelope containing BOTH `\"activity\": []` (always empty in compact mode) and `\"compact_activity\": [...]` (the real rows). Two defects: (1) token waste — a constant dead key ships on every compact query, contrary to the lean-output direction (GH-435 pm-cfed, GH-437 pm-nilh); (2) agent-shape trap — an agent probing `.activity` (or `.entries`) sees a plausible empty array and concludes \"no activity\" instead of erroring, a silent-wrong-answer class worse than a missing key. Fix direction: compact mode should emit ONE canonical key (either reuse `activity` for the compact rows, or omit the empty array entirely); apply the same single-key rule to the MCP pm_run activity envelope and document the shape in contracts. Related: pm-cfed (lean JSON), pm-nilh (lean default), closed pm-ne67 (introduced --compact)."
